20rather%20be%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20could%20hire%20shadow%20stand-ins%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20many%20workplaces%2C%20assuming%20your%20boss%20isn't%20looking%20too%20closely.%20But%20it's%20much%20more%20common%20in%20jobs%20in%20technology%20and%20IT.%20SaaS%20tools%20and%20tech%20services%20like%20Salesforce%2C%20ServiceNow%2C%20and%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%20have%20become%20the%20plumbing%20for%20our%20global%20economy%2C%20used%20by%20everyone%20from%20fast-fashion%20retailers%20to%20nonprofits%2C%20and%20their%20cookie-cutter%20systems%20make%20it%20easy%20for%20anyone%20with%20the%20right%20skills%20to%20quietly%20step%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20an%20American%20Java%20developer%20named%20Kevin%20has%20been%20living%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20outsourcing%20his%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20all%20three%20of%20them.%20With%20the%20help%20of%20a%20Filipino%20friend%20acting%20as%20a%20recruiter%2C%20he%20brought%20on%20three%20local%20%26quot%3Bvirtual%20assistants%2C%26quot%3B%20offloading%20nearly%20all%20of%20his%20technical%20work.%20He%20writes%20formal%20assignment%20sheets%20for%20each%20worker%3B%20%26quot%3BImplement%20a%20test%20for%20valid%20JSON%20in%20POST%20content%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20a%20typical%20directive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeedless%20to%20say%2C%20none%20of%20his%20employers%20%E2%80%94%20finance%20and%20construction%20firms%20%E2%80%94%20know%20about%20one%20another%2C%20and%20his%20workers%20are%20similarly%20in%20the%20dark.%20Even%20his%20location%20is%20a%20secret%3A%20He%20told%20his%20bosses%20he%20was%20based%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20he%20works%20nights%20to%20avoid%20detection.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20low-cost%20labor%20or%20low%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20mostly%2C%26quot%3B%20Kevin%20explained.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20making%20three%20American%20incomes%2C%20but%20I'm%20paying%20Filipino%20rates%20to%20live.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20an%20extreme%20example%20of%20a%20user%20of%20shadow%20stand-ins.%20But%20whether%20they're%20juggling%20multiple%20jobs%20or%20outsourcing%20the%20odd%20task%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20have%20one%20thing%20in%20common%3A%20a%20deep%20skepticism%20of%20traditional%20corporate%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20believe%20if%20the%20work%20gets%20done%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20unconventionally%2C%20there's%20no%20problem.%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20has%20a%20different%20moral%20compass%20and%20a%20different%20thing%20that%20they%20say%3A%20'This%20crosses%20the%20line%20for%20me%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Andrew%2C%20a%20consultant%20in%20Colorado%20who%20has%20outsourced%20work%20to%20freelancers%20and%20family%20members.%20He%20views%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-quitting-hustle-culture-coasting-viral-work-debate-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20quitting%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20deliberately%20coasting%20at%20work%20%E2%80%94%20as%20far%20more%20odious.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20believe%20somebody%20hires%20me%20for%20my%20time.%20They%20hire%20me%20to%20get%20results%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20sits%20on%20top%20of%20a%20food%20chain%20of%20shadow%20workers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6647bc1620abc1efe8fb4f45%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20many%20devotees%2C%20using%20shadow%20stand-ins%20isn't%20just%20a%20preferred%20way%20of%20working%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it's%20a%20renegade%20professional%20philosophy.%3Cp%3ELorenzo%20Matteucci%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%2C%20like%20the%20Southern%20California%20developer%20Brandon%20Nowak%2C%20have%20contemplated%20dipping%20their%20toe%20in%20the%20water.%20He%20told%20me%20that%20shadow%20stand-ins%20are%20an%20inevitable%20outcome%20to%20our%20system%20of%20making%20money.%20%26quot%3BCompanies%20themselves%20are%20taking%20advantage%20of%20you%2C%20by%20hiring%20you%20to%20do%20work%20which%20they%20reap%20more%20value%20from%20you%20than%20they%20give%20to%20you.%20That%20is%20the%20basis%20of%20capitalism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20an%20anti-capitalist%20necessarily%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20fault%20anyone%20%E2%80%94%20myself%20included%20%E2%80%94%20for%20looking%20to%20turn%20those%20tables%20on%20the%20companies%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20one%20wrinkle%20to%20this%20line%20of%20thinking.%20Some%20shadow%20stand-in%20%3Cspan%3Econnoisseurs%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20those%20who%20ship%20their%20work%20to%20offshore%20helpers%20earning%20much%20less%20%E2%80%94%20are%20arguably%20replicating%20the%20same%20structures%20they're%20trying%20to%20rebel%20against.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor-profit%20corporations%20are%20government-sanctioned%20psychopaths%2C%20existing%20only%20to%20predatorily%20and%20parasitically%20earn%20profit%2C%26quot%3B%20Kevin%20said.%20%26quot%3BCorporations%20are%20owed%20no%20moral%20obligation%20whatsoever%2C%20any%20more%20than%20a%20hen%20owes%20a%20fox%20moral%20consideration.%20The%20only%20rational%20response%20is%20to%20extract%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20he%20conceded%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20readily%20admit%20I%20can't%20provide%20a%20consistent%20response%20to%20the%20problem%20of%20pushing%20predator-parasite%20further%20down%20the%20line.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20hiring%20her%20friend%2C%20Remi%20had%20an%20awkward%20realization%3A%20They%20were%20bad%20at%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20they%20made%20glaring%20errors.%20Reformatted%20manuscripts%20came%20back%20with%20page%20numbers%20inserted%20into%20paragraphs%2C%20or%20charts%20were%20missing%20data.%20Remi%20effectively%20demoted%20them%2C%20adjusting%20the%20arrangement%20to%20pay%20%2410%20for%20each%20individual%20chapter%2C%20but%20that%20created%20new%20problems%3A%20Since%20they%20took%20hours%20to%20complete%20what%20usually%20took%20her%2030%20minutes%2C%20she%20was%20effectively%20paying%20them%20less%20than%20minimum%20wage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20friendship%20suffered%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BI'd%20give%20soft%20corrections%20on%20how%20I%20would%20like%20the%20work%20to%20be%20done%2C%20and%20they%20would%20be%20a%20little%20defensive%20about%20it%2C%20or%20wouldn't%20take%20the%20note%2C%26quot%3B%20Remi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20months%2C%20Remi%20decided%20to%20fire%20them%2C%20fibbing%20that%20she%20simply%20no%20longer%20needed%20help.%20She%20turned%20back%20to%20her%20boyfriend%2C%20who%20began%20working%20for%20her%20more%20consistently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dustup%20highlighted%20a%20key%20drawback%20to%20shadow%20stand-ins%3A%20While%20alluring%2C%20things%20can%20go%20horribly%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHalf%20a%20dozen%20workers%20at%20different%20companies%20in%20the%20US%20and%20India%20told%20me%20they%20knew%20of%20colleagues%20who%20had%20secretly%20outsourced%20work.%20Problems%20invariably%20piled%20up%2C%20they%20said%3A%20The%20work%20was%20inadequate%3B%20there%20were%20inconsistencies%20in%20communication%3B%20and%20organizational%20chaos%20abounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can't%20trust%20your%20employee%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they're%20dishonest%20and%20they're%20not%20telling%20you%20the%20truth%20about%20one%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20that%20could%20mean%20that%20they're%20not%20telling%20you%20the%20truth%20about%20other%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Amber%20Clayton%2C%20a%20senior%20director%20at%20the%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%2C%20an%20HR%20industry%20body.%20%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20want%20that%20individual%20within%20the%20organization%2C%20because%20who%20knows%20what%20they%20would%20do%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221348%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20message%20on%20a%20DevOps%20job%20support%20Facebook%20group%20that%20reads%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20individual%20Power%20BI%20Developer%20and%20Administrator%5CnFor%20JOB%20SUPPORT%20%5CnHello%20everyone%2C%5CnI%20am%20in%20urgent%20need%20of%20a%20professional%20with%20extensive%20expertise%20in%20Power%20BI%20development%20and%20administration.%20You%20should%20possess%20at%20least%20six%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20this%20domain%2C%20with%20a%20strong%20command%20of%20DAX%20and%20data%20modeling.%5CnI%20require%20someone%20who%20is%20available%20from%208%20AM%20to%201%20PM%20PST%2C%20Monday%20through%20Friday%2C%20for%20at%20least%202%20hours%20i%20will%20pay%20Rupees%2025%2C000%20with%20biweekly%20payments.%20%5CnInitially%2C%20you%20must%20demonstrate%20the%20capability%20and%20expertise%20within%20the%20first%20two%20days%20.%5CnInterested%20individual%2C%20please%20direct%20message%20me%20to%20discuss%20if%20you're%20available%20to%20provide%20the%20support.%5CnThank%20you.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6647bc7a20abc1efe8fb4f71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22872%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFacebook's%20anonymous%20posting%20tools%20in%20Goups%20have%20made%20it%20easy%20and%20low-risk%20for%20shadow%20stand-in%20seekers%20to%20advertise%20their%20needs.%3Cp%3EFacebook%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20it%20goes%20right%2C%20managing%20a%20secret%20helper%20or%20two%20can%20be%20laborious.%20Your%20conventional%20workload%20may%20be%20lightened%2C%20but%20it's%20replaced%20with%20finding%20and%20vetting%20helpers%2C%20delegating%20tasks%2C%20reviewing%20the%20completed%20work%2C%20and%20living%20in%20constant%20fear%20of%20being%20found%20out.%20%26quot%3BIt%20required%20a%20lot%20of%20micromanaging%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20backend%20engineer%20in%20Pennsylvania%20who%20hired%20shadow%20stand-ins%20to%20help%20him%20juggle%20multiple%20jobs.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20you%20were%20working%20%E2%80%94%20but%20then%20on%20top%20of%20that%2C%20it%20became%20another%20task%20of%20just%20managing%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOccasionally%2C%20the%20problems%20can%20have%20implications%20far%20beyond%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20Tim%20Woodruff%2C%20a%20ServiceNow%20developer%20in%20Washington%20state%2C%20got%20a%20curious%20LinkedIn%20message%20from%20a%20%26quot%3Bconsulting%26quot%3B%20firm.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20send%20job%20applications%20to%20remote%20jobs%20and%20schedule%20job%20interviews%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20message%20read.%20If%20he%20got%20the%20job%2C%20the%20firm%20promised%20to%20%26quot%3Battend%20everything%20related%20to%20programming.%26quot%3B%20All%20he%20had%20to%20do%20for%20whatever%20role%20he%20landed%20was%20attend%20meetings%2C%20and%20give%20the%20firm%20half%20of%20his%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoodruff%20despised%20workplace%20deception%2C%20even%20joining%20job%20support%20and%20proxy%20interview-focused%20Telegram%20groups%20to%20disrupt%20them%20in%20his%20spare%20time.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20autistic%2C%20and%20rules%20help%20me%20make%20sense%20of%20the%20world%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20like%20it%20when%20they're%20just%20ignored%20and%20no%20one%20seems%20to%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20He%20decided%20to%20go%20along%20with%20the%20chicanery%20to%20see%20where%20it%20led.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20joined%20the%20firm's%20Slack%20channel%20and%20let%20it%20apply%20for%20jobs%20on%20his%20behalf%2C%20even%20attending%20some%20job%20interviews.%20He%20said%20he%20noticed%20a%20disquieting%20trend%3A%20Many%20of%20the%20jobs%20he%20was%20interviewing%20for%20had%20national%20security%20implications%2C%20including%20tech%20consultancies%20working%20with%20the%20Secret%20Service%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20the%20Treasury.%20Other%20applications%20were%20to%20financial%20institutions.%20Woodruff%20said%20he%20reported%20the%20firm%20to%20the%20FBI.%20(A%20bureau%20spokesperson%20said%20they%20couldn't%20confirm%20the%20existence%20of%20any%20investigations.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ERanjan%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%20from%20Bengaluru%2C%20is%20regularly%20approached%20by%20job-support%20firms%20trying%20to%20hire%20him%20to%20work%20for%20their%20clients.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20keep%20your%20name%2C%20all%20data%20confidential.%20We%20do%20not%20deduct%20tax%20from%20your%20salary%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20recruiter%20wrote%20to%20him%20on%20LinkedIn.%20%26quot%3BYour%20package%20will%20be%20Beautiful%2C%20trust%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pitch%20hints%20at%20the%20stark%20economic%20power%20disparity%20that%20underpins%20shadow%20stand-ins%2C%20he%20told%20me%3A%20Most%20job%20support%20comes%20from%20countries%20like%20India%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20where%20wages%20are%20low%20and%20%26quot%3Bdesperate%26quot%3B%20workers%20will%20provide%20cheap%20labor.%20Pay%20rates%20for%20shadow%20stand-ins%20are%20%26quot%3Bdefinitely%20more%20than%20what%20people%20earn%20in%20their%20regular%20payday%2C%20that's%20for%20sure%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20mixed%20feelings%20about%20the%20practice%2C%20Kiran%2C%20a%20shadow%20stand-in%20based%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20has%20continued%20to%20provide%20help%20because%20of%20the%20money%20he%20earns.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20faking%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20clients.%20He%20has%20watched%2C%20frustrated%2C%20as%20clients%20coast%20through%20high-paying%20jobs%2C%20lying%20about%20skills%20and%20taking%20job%20opportunities%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20for%20honest%20people%20who%20are%20actually%20experienced.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20sitting%20on%20a%20globe%20with%20shadow%20workers%20in%20the%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6647bce220abc1efe8fb4f96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20same%20economic%20disparities%20that%20underpin%20much%20of%20our%20globalized%20economy%20power%20the%20shadow%20stand-in%20trade%2C%20which%20stretches%20from%20tech%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20to%20low-paid%20helpers%20in%20India.%3Cp%3ELorenzo%20Matteucci%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Western%20pay%20remains%20an%20alluring%20prospect%20to%20many.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20a%20win-win%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rahul%2C%20an%20Indian%20developer%20whose%20friends%20have%20provided%20job%20support%20and%20who%20is%20interested%20in%20doing%20it%20himself.%20%26quot%3BWe%20get%20paid%20peanuts%20anyway%2C%20so%20this%20is%20an%20extra%20source%20of%20income.%20It%20usually%20pays%20better%2C%20too.%26quot%3B%20Andrew%2C%20the%20Colorado%20consultant%2C%20argued%20that%20both%20parties%20agree%20on%20a%20price%20they're%20happy%20with.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20I%20pay%20people%20fairly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Steele%2C%20a%20Michigan%20developer%2C%20has%20an%20Upwork%20account%20and%20receives%20unsolicited%20pitches%20several%20times%20a%20year%20offering%20to%20apply%20for%20and%20complete%20jobs%20using%20his%20name%20in%20return%20for%20a%20slice%20of%20salary.%20%26quot%3BThey%20talk%20about%20how%20getting%20clients%20is%20extremely%20difficult%20when%20you're%20not%20based%20out%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20demand%20has%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20intermediaries%20who%20match%20clients%20and%20helpers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20veritable%20nesting%20doll%20of%20outsourced%20hustle.%20Many%20of%20them%20aren't%20shy%20about%20their%20businesses%3A%20Kumar's%20job%20support%20firm%20Onlinejobsupport.net%2C%20for%20example%2C%20claims%20on%20its%20website%20to%20have%20more%20than%20500%20happy%20clients%20across%2025%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20focusing%20on%20popular%20systems%20or%20tools%20like%20Java%2C%20AWS%2C%20Hadoop%2C%20and%20React.%20(It%20might%20be%20wise%20to%20be%20skeptical%20of%20any%20one%20provider's%20marketing%20claims%2C%20but%20there's%20clearly%20a%20bustling%20ecosystem.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20intermediaries%20aren't%20shy%20about%20their%20business%2C%20either.%20You%20can%20even%20find%20some%20marketing%20their%20services%20on%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20years%20were%20a%20boom%20time%20for%20shadow%20stand-ins.%20Now%20the%20winds%20are%20shifting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReturn-to-office%20has%20forced%20some%20delegators%20to%20give%20it%20up%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20harder%20to%20screen-share%20and%20outsource%20tasks%20if%20you're%20sitting%20in%20a%20cubicle%20%E2%80%94%20while%20others%20are%20reduced%20to%20huddling%20with%20helpers%20after%20returning%20home.%20Providers%20told%20me%20they're%20feeling%20the%20pinch%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20putting%20the%20genie%20back%20in%20the%20bottle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20model%20has%20been%20proved%2C%20the%20global%20supply%20chain%20is%20there%2C%20and%20worker%20attitudes%20have%20shifted.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20died%20at%20my%20desk%20tomorrow%2C%20my%20job%20would%20be%20posted%20online%20before%20my%20funeral%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20Oregon%20worker%20whose%20colleague%20tried%20to%20outsource%20their%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOthers%20question%20why%20secret%20delegating%20might%20be%20stigmatized%20more%20than%20other%20tactics.%20%26quot%3BAssuming%20you%20are%20not%20sharing%20proprietary%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrew%2C%20the%20Colorado%20consultant%2C%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20is%20the%20difference%20from%20outsourcing%20your%20work%20vs%20using%20an%20AI%20or%20software%20tool%20to%20automate%20your%20work%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20shadow%20stand-ins%20feel%20like%20a%20uniquely%20modern%2C%20internet-enabled%20phenomenon%2C%20its%20roots%20run%20much%20deeper.%20%26quot%3BHistorically%2C%20at%20least%20in%20certain%20trades%2C%20both%20in%20the%20US%20and%20other%20countries%2C%20the%20household%20unit%20was%20the%20unit%20employed%20to%20do%20the%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michel%20Anteby%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20sociology%20at%20Boston%20University.%20He%20offered%20up%20the%20New%20England%20spinning%20industry%20as%20an%20example.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20really%20cared%20or%20tracked%20if%20it%20was%20the%20husband%2C%20the%20wife%2C%20the%20kids%20who%20are%20doing%20the%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemi%20fits%20neatly%20within%20that%20framework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20boyfriend%2C%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20was%20a%20great%20worker.%20He%20could%20swiftly%20complete%20technical%20tasks%20that%20usually%20took%20her%20all%20day%2C%20and%20she%20didn't%20pay%20him%3B%20they%20had%20already%20merged%20finances%20when%20her%20mother%20died.%20They%20continued%20the%20arrangement%20until%20she%20quit%20a%20year%20later.%20But%20even%20after%20she%20left%2C%20Remi%20received%20intermittent%20texts%20from%20old%20coworkers%20asking%20for%20help.%20She%20never%20replied.%20She%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20letting%20the%20company%20exploit%20her%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20Chicagoan%20has%20no%20regrets.%20%26quot%3BI%20personally%20come%20from%20a%20background%20where%20I%20am%20very%20anti-corporation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20personally%20see%20the%20harm%20in%20it%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20because%20if%20my%20company%20isn't%20going%20to%20do%20its%20best%20to%20keep%20me%20happy%20and%20healthy%2C%20and%20have%20my%20best%20interests%20in%20mind%2C%20then%20that%20falls%20upon%20me%20to%20ensure%20that%20that's%20happening%20for%20myself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemi%20now%20works%20in%20an%20education-related%20field.%20Her%20boyfriend%20is%20employed%20as%20a%20remedial%20tutor%20at%20a%20school%2C%20and%20she%20sometimes%20lends%20him%20a%20hand%2C%20formatting%20his%20presentation%20slides%20and%20doing%20other%20miscellaneous%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3