tch-meet-up-and-massive-bill-the-modus-operandi-in-dating-app-scams-6001555%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Secret%20Dossier%20Reveals%20Queen%20Elizabeth%20I's%20Network%20Of%20Spies%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EA%20document%20titled%20%26quot%3BThe%20Names%20of%20the%20Intelligencers%26quot%3B%20has%20now%20disclosed%20the%20hidden%20network%20of%20spies%20of%20England%20and%20Ireland's%20former%20Queen%20Elizabeth%20I.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20single%20sheet%20of%20paper%20has%20been%20lying%20undisturbed%20in%20the%20National%20Archives%20for%20over%20a%20century%2C%20as%20per%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2Farticle%2F2024%2Fjun%2F29%2Funcovered-428-year-old-secret-dossier-reveals-elizabeth-is-network-of-spies%C2%A0%5C%22%3EGuardian%3C%2Fa%3E%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20also%20mentioned%20that%20this%20paper%20is%20part%20of%20a%20428-year-old%C2%A0secret%20dossier%20that%20once%20belonged%20to%20Robert%20Cecil%2C%20the%20spymaster%20for%20Queen%20Elizabeth.%20Cecil%20is%20also%20the%20man%20who%20discovered%20the%20Gunpowder%20Plot%20in%201605.%20Putting%20this%20document%20together%20with%20the%20dossier%20shows%20how%20Cecil%20used%20a%20secret%20spy%20network%20to%20watch%20European%20kings%20and%20queens%20for%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHistorian%20Stephen%20Alford%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20professor%20of%20early%20modern%20British%20history%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Leeds%2C%20found%20the%20list%20nearly%2015%20years%20ago.%20He%20believes%20it%20was%20England's%20%E2%80%9Cfirst%20properly%20organised%20secret%20service%E2%80%9D.%20Alford%20has%20been%20working%20to%20reconstruct%20Cecil's%20files%20on%20each%20spy%20ever%20since%20he%20found%20the%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20lots%20of%20names%20listed%20%E2%80%93%20some%20I%20recognised%2C%20people%20in%20or%20close%20to%20the%20privy%20council%20of%20Elizabeth%20I%2C%20and%20lots%20I%20didn't%20know.%20Eventually%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20the%20numbers%20next%20to%20their%20names%20were%20folio%20numbers%20and%20that%20this%20was%20really%20a%20contents%20page.%20That%20was%20a%20lightbulb%20moment%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Mr%20Alford%20as%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20list%20of%20spies%20had%20been%20placed%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmiscellaneous%E2%80%9D%20folder%20by%20Victorian%20archivists.%20As%20per%20Mr%20Alford's%20beliefs%2C%20Cecil%20began%20to%20write%20the%20document%20in%201596.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMr%20Alford%20thinks%20that%20he%20is%20%E2%80%9Cprobably%20the%20first%20scholar%E2%80%9D%20to%20take%20an%20interest%20in%20this%20document.%20He%20also%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Victorians%20had%20a%20habit%2C%20where%20if%20they%20came%20across%20papers%20that%20didn't%20make%20sense%20to%20them%2C%20that%20were%20a%20little%20mysterious%20and%20couldn't%20be%20filed%20away%20in%20a%20neat%20and%20tidy%20way%2C%20they%20would%20scratch%20their%20heads%20and%20then%20stick%20them%20in%20a%20miscellaneous%20folder%20and%20ignore%20them.%20And%20that's%20where%20historians%20now%20find%20really%20interesting%20stuff.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMr%20Alford%20searched%20through%20old%20archives%20for%20relevant%20papers%20marked%20with%20small%20numbers%20matching%20the%20index.%20Many%20papers%20were%20damaged%20from%20poor%20storage%20in%20the%20Tower%20of%20London%2C%20often%20by%20rats%20and%20mice%20leaving%20stains%20and%20even%20bite%20marks.%20Despite%20these%20challenges%2C%20the%20documents%20survived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBefore%20Mr%20Alford's%20research%2C%20scholars%20believed%20Cecil%20had%20only%20a%20few%20scattered%20spies.%20However%2C%20he%20discovered%20Cecil%20had%20a%20well-organised%20network%20of%20over%2020%20spies%20in%20cities%20like%20Lisbon%2C%20Calais%2C%20Brussels%2C%20Seville%2C%20Rome%2C%20Amsterdam%2C%20Scotland%2C%20Sweden%2C%20and%20other%20places.%20Mr%20Alford%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CHe%20(Cecil)%20chose%20merchants%20because%20they%20travel%2C%20can%20read%20and%20write%2C%20speak%20European%20languages%20and%20have%20networks%20of%20their%20own.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719732420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fujrt0tv_elizabeth_625x300_30_June_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsecrets-of-elizabeth-is-spy-network-revealed-in-428-year-old-dossier-6001605%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20document%20titled%20%26quot%3BThe%20Names%20of%20the%20Intelligencers%26quot%3B%20has%20now%20disclosed%20the%20hidden%20network%20of%20spies%20of%20England%20and%20Ireland's%20former%20Queen%20Elizabeth%20I.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsecrets-of-elizabeth-is-spy-network-revealed-in-428-year-old-dossier-6001605%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsecrets-of-elizabeth-is-spy-network-revealed-in-428-year-old-dossier-6001605%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsecrets-of-elizabeth-is-spy-network-revealed-in-428-year-old-dossier-6001605%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shraddha%20says%20%E2%80%98Tabiyat%20down%20aahe%2C%E2%80%99%20at%20airport%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719731417000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111377531%2Cimgsize-67702.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshraddha-kapoor-says-tabiyat-down-aahe-as-paps-asks-her-to-remove-the-mask%2Farticleshow%2F111377531.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20borde